    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="539"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d539fn1">Sent via the White House Map Room and the British
                        Admiralty Delegation at Washington. Churchill was in Canada at this
                        time.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-26">August 26,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to <gloss target="#t_CW1">Colonel Warden</gloss>, Personal and
                    Secret. Number 347. I hope you have seen Uncle Joe’s new message<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d539fn2">i.e., Stalin’s message of August 24, 1943, which had just
                        reached Roosevelt at Hyde Park. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1174">p. 1174</ref>.</note> which is <pb facs="1293"
                        n="1179" xml:id="pg_1179"/> greatly improved in its tone. As you and he
                    know, I am lost until Monday and I would let a few days go by till we answer
                    him.</p>
                <p>However, my first feeling is that he has come around to our secondary meeting and
                    that it should be held very soon.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
